uk.co.indigo.play.rfid.print.gui
Class RFIDPrintHelper

java.lang.Object
  uk.co.indigo.play.rfid.print.gui.RFIDPrintHelper

public class RFIDPrintHelper
extends java.lang.Object

This is the controller that provides API proxies for the encode and print functions. It is called by the view: RFIDPrintSWT.

encode

public static java.lang.String encode(java.lang.String hv,
                                      java.lang.String fv,
                                      java.lang.String pv,
                                      java.lang.String cpi,
                                      java.lang.String sr,
                                      java.lang.String ed,
                                      java.lang.String cd)
A controller proxy to the SSCC encoding services.

Parameters:
hv - A decimal String representation of the header value.
fv - A decimal String representation of the filter value.
pv - A decimal String representation of the partition value.
cpi - A decimal String representation of the company partition prefix.
sr - A decimal String representation of the serial reference.
ed - A decimal String representation of the extension digit.
cd - A decimal String representation of the check digit.
Returns:
A String representation of the hex encoded binary SSCC.

print

public static void print(java.lang.String printerName,
                         java.lang.String data,
                         int quantity)
                  throws PrintException
Parameters:
printerName - Must be a valid printer name as determined by uk.co.indigo.play.rfid.print.PrintController factory method.
data - Raw hex data representation of the SSCC.
quantity - The number of SSCC labels to print.
Throws:
PrintException - Thrown on problems with the print template or the queue.

acquireTemplate

                                         throws PrintException
Returns:
A String containing the template text for an SSCC96 print job.
Throws:
PrintException - Thrown on problems finding or loading the template file.

queuePrintJob

Parameters:
jobName - A name for the job. Should be unique.
job - The data filled version of the template.
